Nigeria’s SEC Sets Up Group to Examine Demutualization of Bourse

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-09-29T08:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/nigeria-s-sec-sets-up-group-to-examine-demutualization-of-bourse.html
Nigeria ’s Securities and Exchange
Commission has set up a technical committee to advise on the
possible demutualization of the  Nigerian Stock Exchange .  The committee,which was inaugurated last week, has three
months to come up with recommendations, Udoma Udo Udoma,
chairman of Nigeria’s SEC, said at a conference in Johannesburg
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
